---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Glossary" description="Key financial terms used throughout this guide.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pb-12 pt-16 sm:px-6">
    <h1>Glossary</h1>
    <p class="mb-8 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
      Quick definitions for terms used in this guide.
    </p>

    <dl class="space-y-6">
      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">401k</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          An employer-sponsored retirement savings plan with tax advantages. Traditional 401k
          contributions are pre-tax; Roth 401k contributions are after-tax. <a
            href="/guide/3-investment-accounts">More &rarr;</a
          >
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Asset allocation</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          How your portfolio is divided among different asset classes (stocks, bonds, cash). The
          primary driver of your portfolio's risk and return. <a href="/guide/4-investment-choices"
            >More &rarr;</a
          >
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Asset location</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Placing specific investments in the most tax-efficient account type. Different from asset <em
            >allocation</em
          >.
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Bear market</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          A stock market decline of 20% or more from a recent peak. Historically occurs every 4-6
          years. <a href="/guide/5-staying-the-course">More &rarr;</a>
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Beneficiary</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          The person designated to receive account assets after the owner's death. Beneficiary
          designations override wills. <a href="/guide/6-next-steps">More &rarr;</a>
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Bond</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          A loan you make to a government or corporation. Bonds pay interest and are generally less
          volatile than stocks. <a href="/guide/4-investment-choices">More &rarr;</a>
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Compound interest</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Earning returns on your returns. $10,000 growing at 8% becomes $10,800 after year one,
          then $11,664 after year two (8% of $10,800, not $10,000).
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Debt-to-income ratio (DTI)</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Total monthly debt payments divided by gross monthly income. Used by lenders to evaluate
          borrowing capacity. <a href="/guide/2-tackle-debt">More &rarr;</a>
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Diversification</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Spreading investments across many assets to reduce risk. A fund holding 3,000+ stocks is
          highly diversified; a portfolio of 5 tech stocks is not.
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">ETF (Exchange-Traded Fund)</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          A fund that trades on a stock exchange. Most ETFs are index funds. <a
            href="/guide/4-investment-choices">More &rarr;</a
          >
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Expense ratio (ER)</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          The annual fee charged by a fund, expressed as a percentage. A 0.03% ER on $100,000 costs
          $30/year. <a href="/guide/4-investment-choices">More &rarr;</a>
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Fiduciary</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          A professional legally obligated to act in your best interest, not their own. Always hire
          a fiduciary financial advisor. <a href="/guide/6-next-steps">More &rarr;</a>
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">
          HYSA (High-Yield Savings Account)
        </dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          An online savings account paying significantly more interest than a traditional one. <a
            href="/guide/1-cash-cushion">More &rarr;</a
          >
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">HSA (Health Savings Account)</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Triple tax advantage: deductible contributions, tax-free growth, tax-free withdrawals for
          medical expenses. <a href="/guide/3-investment-accounts">More &rarr;</a>
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Index fund</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          A fund that tracks a market index by owning all or most stocks in that index. Low cost,
          broadly diversified, consistently outperforms most active funds. <a
            href="/guide/4-investment-choices">More &rarr;</a
          >
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">
          IRA (Individual Retirement Account)
        </dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          A retirement account you open yourself. Traditional may be tax-deductible; Roth
          contributions are after-tax but withdrawals are tax-free. <a
            href="/guide/3-investment-accounts">More &rarr;</a
          >
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Rebalancing</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Periodically buying and selling to return your portfolio to its target allocation. <a
            href="/guide/4-investment-choices">More &rarr;</a
          >
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Roth</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          A tax treatment where you pay taxes now but all growth and qualified withdrawals are
          tax-free. Available for 401k and IRA. <a href="/guide/3-investment-accounts"
            >More &rarr;</a
          >
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Savings rate</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          The percentage of gross income directed toward building wealth. A key metric for financial
          progress. <a href="/guide/0-before-you-start">More &rarr;</a>
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Target date fund</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          A single fund that holds stocks and bonds and automatically adjusts over time, becoming
          more conservative as the target date approaches. <a href="/guide/4-investment-choices"
            >More &rarr;</a
          >
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Treasury bill (T-bill)</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          A short-term U.S. government bond (4 weeks to 1 year). Considered risk-free. Often used
          for the conservative tier of an emergency fund. <a href="/guide/1-cash-cushion"
            >More &rarr;</a
          >
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
